    <div class="comment-text editable-message-text" itemprop="commentText"><p>To test:</p>
<p>1. Install Moodle and Mahara. Enable Mnet on both.<br />
2. Create an institution in Mahara with an XMLRPC auth instance, using Moodle and the &quot;They SSO in&quot; setting.<br />
3. Set up Moodle so that your users can roam over to Mahara via MNet.<br />
4. Set the Mahara institution&#x27;s expiration date to the past, and/or suspend the Mahara institution.<br />
5. Log in to Moodle.<br />
6. Roam over to Mahara.</p>
<p>Expected result: When you try to roam over to Mahara, you can&#x27;t log in, because your institution is expired.</p>
<p>Actual result: You roam to Mahara with no problem.</p></div>
    
    
    
